content:
@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #80950 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?

From the issue:

This is likely to be closed with wont-fix, but I wanted to ensure it was noted somewhere.

We should probably de-I-prioritize.
Yea I'm not really sure what's supposed to happen with this. It simply seemed like a good idea to make note of it
I've labeled T-compiler so it does not slip through our filters
Unless we want to bring to anyone's attention we can probably close it? Although I'd see some value in notifying the crates' maintaners about that (if it provides actionable inputs for them)
At least one of them is a Advent of Code repo so I'm not so sure how much utility it will bring to notify
@rylev which crates are failing? I've tried parsing the crate run logs but I could not immediately find the regressions due to Ord::clamp and bool::then
https://crates.io/crates/ticklock/0.0.8 is actually the only crate on crates.io. The rest were GitHub repos
